MATCH data readers
doc last changed: 9/18/97
code changes:
  11/19/97: fix "-DREALSIZE=8"

Overview
-------
MATCH has defined a general interface to get dynamics data, so that it
can be driven with different datasets. See doc/dynamics_input_data
for details.

The "standard" reader is for CCM2/3 output, and comes standard with the
match release.  The interface code is implemented in dyninp.F.

Other sets of routines implement alternative readers. Currently, the ncep 
reader can read NCEP/NCAR reanalysis output.

Modifying the Match release
---------------------------
In general, to use these readers, you modify the match Makefile, removing
dyninp.F, and adding the new set of code.  Since we expect for match to continue
to evolve, the general idea is to be able to copy the match release to the top
level directory, untar it, modify the Makefile, and remake.  Therefore, we keep 
the reader source in seperate directory, but build in the match directory. (Another 
idea is to keep the match source in a different directory, and have "build"
directories for different target machines. Not yet implemented).

Some specific notes on needed modifications:

On machines with access to the NCAR MSS (via the msread command)
add -DHAS_MSREAD to compile line for mss.c

The Readers
-----------
Each reader subdirectory has an example Makefile that you need to manually merge with 
the standard match Makefile.  

The following routines are common utilities, and are kept in match/readers:
    mss.[ch]         mass store files management
    str_util.[ch]    string utilities
    utim.[ch]        time conversion utilities
    rgi.[ch]	     Area Average regridding
    rgip.F	     fortran routines for regridding

The reader specific routines are kept in readers/<readername>

